comments.body:
Talked more with [~rusvika]. The way to reproduce this is:

- have the 2 CC working (enabled/disabled);
- add the preload on both machines;
   - on the secondary the rules in preload will be loaded in iptables
   - on the primary the preload rules will not be loaded;
- afterward, stop primary CC to force a failover
- the rules will not be apply until a cleanrestart is issued.

Expected behavior: the CC should be able to pick up the rules either dynamically (as soon as the file is changed), or upon failover the rules should stay loaded.
